TELEGRAM
  Send a message to another country.

SYNTAX
  telegram <cnum> <message>
  tele     <cnum> <message>
  pray     <message>           (sends to deity, country 0)

DESCRIPTION
  Sends a telegram to another country.  Telegrams are received
  immediately and can be read with the 'read' command.

  <cnum>     - country number to send to
  <message>  - the message text (rest of command line)

  'pray' is a shortcut to send a message to the deity (country 0),
  useful for reporting bugs or requesting help.

  Telegrams are stored until read.  The recipient sees a notification
  of unread telegrams when they log in.

EXAMPLE
  telegram 3 Interested in an alliance?
  tele 2 I have iron to trade, interested?
  pray The gold mine at -3,1 seems broken

SEE ALSO
